{
  "texts": [
    "Recurrent neural networks (RNN) can extract patterns in sequences of data that are dynamic and temporal in nature.",
    "The ability to extract patterns from sequences is provided by recurrent hidden states.",
    "One disadvantage of conventional RNN is the vanishing gradient or exploding gradient due to long-term sequential data which downgrades performance of RNN.",
    "To overcome this issue, Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) (Graves, 2013) and Gated Recurrent Unit (GRU) (Chung et al., 2014) were introduced.",
    "A hyperspectral data cube is a 3D dataset; each sample of the data cube serves as sequential data for the RNN."
  ]
}